<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2007-09-24</DATELINE><TITLE>BK Virus Replication In Vitro: Limited Effect of Drugs Interfering with Viral Uptake and Intracellular Transport</TITLE><BODY>BK virus is an important pathogen in kidney transplant recipients. In vitro studies demonstrated slight antiviral activity for chloroquine and nystatin. A sialic acid derivative, BTB11968, was identified as a lead compound for further development.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>